# Install Node JS

This uses a similar scheme as the multiple GHC version

* Download X64 version from [https://nodejs.org/en/download/](https://nodejs.org/en/download/)

~~~
    cd Download
    NODE_VERSION="v4.5.0"
    tar xf node-$NODE_VERSION-linux-x64.tar.xz
    sudo cp -rp node-$NODE_VERSION-linux-x64 /usr/local/
    sudo ln -s /usr/local/node-$NODE_VERSION-linux-x64 /usr/local/node
~~~

* Add /usr/local/node/bin to the $PATH in .profile

# Update / Upgrade NodeJS

Use module n to install the newest stable version

     
    sudo npm install n -g
    sudo n stable

   

